entries.femaleVariant: You River Ward?
Detective Ward?
Someone here to see you, looks like.
In the flesh. V, right?
My partner, Detective Han.
Red Queen's Race – heard anything about it? Know what it is?
Maybe I have, maybe I do. It got anything to do with Rhyne?
Guy was headed there the day he died.
entries.maleVariant: The guy was headed there the day he died.

entries.femaleVariant: Pssh... fine. We're gonna see my CI.
All I've heard, it's some fancy-ass club. No idea where to even look for it. CI might know.
Let's go see his boss.
Let's meet with your CI.
Let's go see his boss first. Guy who can afford all the chrome he was decked out in should have the scratch for psychomuting meds too.
entries.maleVariant: Let's go see his boss first. The guy who can afford all the chrome he was decked out in should have the scratch for psychomuting meds too.

entries.femaleVariant: Let's go see your informer. Club's a better lead.
OK.
Fine with me.
Thanks for agreeing to meet.
Don't know what I intend just yet. For now, gonna see if I hear anything new about Rhyne's death.
You back on that? Boss already told you to drop it. Don't make him say it again. You know he hates to say things twice.
And if you couldn't give a rat's fat ass about any of that, heed my advice, as your friend's. Just let the case go.
See me doin' anything? Just sittin' here, sippin' coffee, listenin' to gossip.
Fine. Do what you want. I'm not about to be part of this. Gotta go get my little girl anyway.
And you two at least find a quieter corner. Wouldn't wanna be overheard.
OK, talk.
OK. Thanks for agreeing to meet.
You really intend to work with a merc?
Before the attack, you wanted to talk to Rhyne's huscle, get some info to 'em.
entries.maleVariant: Before the attack, you wanted to talk to Rhyne's huscle, get some info to them.

entries.femaleVariant: Liz Peralez hired me. And her husband, Jefferson.
[Sit] Partner's not a fan of edgerunners.
See Detective Han's not a fan of edgerunners.
entries.maleVariant: I see Detective Han's not a fan of edgerunners.

entries.femaleVariant: Don't take it personally. Detective Han's not a fan of anybody. 'Cept his daughter.
What was it?
Some of the boys from the precinct saw Horváth around Arroyo, shooting up dumpsters, hollering how he's got a meet with the mayor. Brought 'im in.
Let me ask you a question first. Why do you got your nose in this? Who hired you?
Péter Horváth. Cyberpsycho who attacked the mayor later. They took him downtown, but then he got "lost" before they could get his statement.
So you decided to warn the mayor?
He got lost – what do you mean?
Sorry, never give up the names of my clients.
Said he "got lost." How's that happen, what's it mean?
entries.maleVariant: Said he "got lost." How's that happen? What's it mean?

entries.femaleVariant: So you saw him as a potential threat, decided to warn the mayor?
Just like that, 'cause… ya got a good heart?
Make it sound like that's somethin' to be ashamed of.
Ashamed – no. Just not somethin' you see every day.
entries.maleVariant: Ashamed – nah. Just not somethin' you see every day.

entries.femaleVariant: It means someone didn't want him counting roaches in a cell that day.
And before you ask me, no... I got no idea who.
Brought who in?
My turn. Why's Peralez looking at this now? Why's he want it done unofficial, on the hush-hush?
Well then, I'm sure you've got plenty of other leads besides me. I mean, I sure hope so, 'cause I'm not telling you a thing.
And I'm not bein' mean, or nosy, nor is it personal. Just coverin' my own ass, my own safety's at stake too.
Workin' for the Peralezes.
Won't give you my client's name.
So... before I open my mouth, I need to know whose ears are listenin'.
The presumed future mayor? Haha... Guess I could've seen that comin'…
Know what... Han was right. Acoustics are a little too good in here.
Got my car outside.
[Stand] OK.
OK, sure.
Red Queen's Race – know what it is?
Think Peralez is gonna try to smear Holt.
As I see it, Peralez is out to smear Holt.
Peralez might be scared.
Peralez could just be scared.
So he thinks Holt's involved?
Dunno. But even if he's not, a murdered mayor isn't great optics for his deputy.
Doesn't want the job of a guy who just got carried out feet first?
Heh, who would?
Then we'll go talk to the woman Horváth worked for.
Or actually... we could see her first. Up to you.
"We"?
Sorry – "we"?
Can't shake this case. Something's up. Just look at how quickly it was closed.
This way, you can get your job done while I find evidence that gets my chief to re-open the case.
Win-win. So, where to first?
We'd better check it out.
You wanted to talk?
Got a quiet one here.
Well? Come on.
[Sit] What'd you wanna tell the mayor?
Hm. Wonder what about…
Like to talk to you.
Wanted to talk. You got a minute?
You must be V.
My partner, Detective Han.
Step off to the side, talk alone – can we?
Mind if we step off to the side?
entries.maleVariant: Y'mind if we step off to the side?

entries.femaleVariant: Han and me, we're like one mind. Got no secrets.
[Sit and wait]
[Get in]
